imdb.title: Sutoraiku uicchîzu
imdb.plot: The story takes place in year 1944 and the world lives in fear of unidentified flying objects called neuroi. A young heroine Named Yoshika miyafuji joins the 501st joint wing, known as the strike witches to fight and defeat the ne...

episodes.title: Futatabi Sora e
episodes.plot: Yoshika's plans to become a doctor are put on hold after a mysterious letter from her father leads to a reunion with Sakamoto. Elsewhere, her former Strike Witch comrades take to the air to battle a new breed of Neuroi!

episodes.title: Densetsu no Majotachi
episodes.plot: When Sakamoto's strike unit malfunctions, Yoshika is forced into a solo dogfight against a rapidly-regenerating Neuroi! The bombastic beauties of the 501st Joint Fighter Wing race to provide backup, but will they arrive in time?

episodes.title: Issho ni Dekiru Koto
episodes.plot: Yoshika, Lynne, and Perrine report to a mysterious old woman for some special training, but their broomstick lessons are soon interrupted by a deadly Neuroi attack!

episodes.title: Katai, Hayai, Monosugoi
episodes.plot: Barkhorn runs into big trouble during a test flight of the new jet striker unit, and only an extremely well-endowed comrade has the power to save her from the ultimate crash-landing!

episodes.title: Watashi no Romanya
episodes.plot: A Strike Witch shopping trip goes up in flames when Lucchini spends the squadron's money on a sightseeing adventure and the town is attacked by Neuroi!

episodes.title: Sora yori Takaku
episodes.plot: A menacing new breed of Neuroi looms high above the clouds, and the Strike Witches must equip themselves with experimental rocket boosters in order to reach the unprecedented altitude required to destroy their enemy!

episodes.title: Mozomozo Suru no
episodes.plot: Bath time is interrupted by an invasive insect hopping from one set of skimpy skivvies to another. The Strike Witches are up in arms over this shocking breach of their britches, and they'll do whatever it takes to protect their panties!

episodes.title: Tsubasa wo Kudasai
episodes.plot: Yoshika is permanently grounded after suddenly losing the ability to fly, but a prototype Striker Unit inspired by her father's letter may hold the key to putting her back in action!

episodes.title: Asu ni Kakeru Hashi
episodes.plot: When the girls of the 501st hit the beach for some special training, Lucchini discovers a treasure chest that leads to a treasure map that leads to booby traps!

episodes.title: 500 Overs
episodes.plot: Hartmann teams up with a famous witch on loan from another unit in order to defeat a special Neuroi that's impervious to airborne attacks! The new girl has lethal skills - and an attitude to match!

episodes.title: Watashi de Aru Tame Ni
episodes.plot: As the Strike Witches prepare for their most dangerous mission yet, Major Sakamoto - the bravest warrior among their ranks - can no longer hide the fact that her magic is rapidly fading!

episodes.title: Sora Yori Towa Ni
episodes.plot: Major Sakamoto risks her life to save the world, but the Neuroi hive proves nearly impossible to destroy. The witches are all out of magic, but Yoshika refuses to give up the fight!

episodes.title: Mahô shôjo
episodes.plot: Yoshika's powerful healing spell catches the eye of Major Sakamoto - who attempts to recruit her for a high-flying military unit known as the Strike Witches.

episodes.title: Watashi ni dekirukoto
episodes.plot: Major Sakamoto flies into action when a Neuroi attacks her ship. Yoshika is mesmerized by the weapons her father invented, but does she have the courage to use them?

episodes.title: Hitori ja nai kara
episodes.plot: Yoshika is introduced to the rest of the Strike Witches and begins her grueling training. When the Neuroi strike unexpectedly, she gets a chance to test her mettle.

episodes.title: Arigatô
episodes.plot: Lt. Barkhorn's reckless battle tactics put her life in great danger; Yoshika and Perrine must set aside their differences and work together to save her.

episodes.title: Hayai, okkî, yawarakai
episodes.plot: Yoshika keeps having strange, exciting dreams about her fellow Strike Witches and a surprise enemy attack may actually make them come true.

episodes.title: Issho dayo
episodes.plot: An unexpected encounter with the rapidly-adapting Neuroi convinces Major Sakamoto to form a night patrol led by Sanya - who happens to share a birthday with Yoshika.

episodes.title: Sû sû suruno
episodes.plot: When Hartmann's underwear vanishes, it leads to game of musical panties that's got all the Strike Witches jumping in and out of their skivvies.

episodes.title: Kimi o wasurenai
episodes.plot: As the fleet prepares for a daring counter-offensive, Commander Minna searches for the courage to face the reminders of her tragic past.

episodes.title: Mamoritaimono
episodes.plot: Minna and Sakamoto argue over the Major's future with the Strike Witches. A close encounter with an unusual Neuroi lures Yoshika into a trap.

episodes.title: Shinjitehoshî
episodes.plot: Yoshika is placed on house arrest for her part in Major Sakamoto's injury, but she can't shake the feeling that the witch-shaped Neuroi is somehow different from the others.

episodes.title: Sora e...
episodes.plot: The Strike Witches are disbanded in favor of more advanced military technology - the Warlock. But as the girls go their separate ways, something goes horribly wrong.

episodes.title: Sutoraiku uicchîzu
episodes.plot: Yoshika battles the out-of-control Warlock, but it's too much for her to handle. At the moment she needs them most, the Strike Witches reassemble and join the fight!
